# Lab 4 – Conceptual Design of an IIoT Sensor Network & Protocol Experimentation
https://github.com/ChadJon/L04_Chad-Jones_Group-8_ITAI_3377

## Overview
This lab focused on designing an Industrial Internet of Things (IIoT) sensor network and exploring how communication protocols impact system performance.

The goal was to understand how devices in an IIoT environment communicate, how data flows through the system, and how different protocols affect reliability, latency, and scalability.

## Objectives
- Design a conceptual IIoT sensor network
- Understand communication protocols (MQTT, HTTP, etc.)
- Evaluate how data is transmitted between devices and systems
- Analyze efficiency and reliability in industrial environments

## What We Did
- Designed a network including sensors, gateways, and cloud components
- Explored how devices communicate using different protocols
- Compared advantages and disadvantages of each protocol
- Analyzed how network design affects performance and scalability

## Key Concepts Learned
- IIoT systems rely heavily on efficient communication
- Protocol choice affects speed, reliability, and energy usage
- Gateways are critical for connecting edge devices to the cloud
- Scalability is a major concern in industrial environments

## Challenges
- Understanding how protocols differ in real-world use
- Visualizing how all components connect together
- Balancing performance vs. complexity in system design

## Simple Reflection
This lab helped me understand how important communication is in IoT systems. Before this, I didn’t realize how much the choice of protocol can impact performance. It also showed me that designing a system is not just about connecting devices, but making sure everything works efficiently together.
